<subpara id="RM000000PFB017X_07" type-id="51" category="05" proc-id="RM0250U___00002JA00000">
<name>INSPECTION PROCEDURE</name>
<content5 releasenbr="1">
<atten4>
<list1 type="unordered">
<item>
<ptxt>If any of DTCs P0115, P0117, P0118 or P0125 are set simultaneously with DTC P0116, the ECT sensor may have an open or a short circuit. Troubleshoot those DTCs first.</ptxt>
</item>
<item>
<ptxt>Read freeze frame data using the intelligent tester. The ECM records vehicle and driving condition information as freeze frame data the moment a DTC is stored. When troubleshooting, freeze frame data can be helpful in determining whether the vehicle was running or stopped, whether the engine was warmed up or not, whether the air-fuel ratio was lean or rich, as well as other data recorded at the time of a malfunction (See page <xref label="Seep01" href="RM000000PDS00ZX"/>).</ptxt>
</item>
</list1>
</atten4>
</content5>
</subpara>
<subpara id="RM000000PFB017X_08" type-id="01" category="01">
<name>PROCEDURE</name>
<testgrp id="RM000000PFB017X_08_0001" proc-id="RM0250U___00002JB00000">
<testtitle>CHECK OTHER DTC OUTPUT (IN ADDITION TO DTC P0116)</testtitle>
<content6 releasenbr="1">
<test1>
<ptxt>Connect the intelligent tester to the DLC3.</ptxt>
</test1>
<test1>
<ptxt>Turn the ignition switch on (IG).</ptxt>
</test1>
<test1>
<ptxt>Turn the tester on.</ptxt>
</test1>
<test1>
<ptxt>Enter the following menus: DIAGNOSIS / ENHANCED II / DTC INFO / CURRENT CODES.</ptxt>
</test1>
<test1>
<ptxt>Read the DTC.</ptxt>
<spec>
<title>Result</title>
<table pgwide="1">
<tgroup cols="2" align="center">
<colspec colname="COL1" colwidth="3.54in"/>
<colspec colname="COL2" colwidth="3.54in"/>
<thead>
<row>
<entry valign="middle">
<ptxt>Display (DTC output)</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry valign="middle">
<ptxt>Proceed to</ptxt>
</entry>
</row>
</thead>
<tbody>
<row>
<entry valign="middle">
<ptxt>P0116</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry valign="middle">
<ptxt>A</ptxt>
</entry>
</row>
<row>
<entry valign="middle">
<ptxt>P0116 and other DTCs</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry valign="middle">
<ptxt>B</ptxt>
</entry>
</row>
</tbody>
</tgroup>
</table>
</spec>
</test1>
</content6>
<res>
<down ref="RM000000PFB017X_08_0006" fin="false">A</down>
<right ref="RM000000PFB017X_08_0003" fin="true">B</right>
</res>
</testgrp>
<testgrp id="RM000000PFB017X_08_0006" proc-id="RM0250U___00002JC00000">
<testtitle>INSPECT THERMOSTAT</testtitle>
<content6 releasenbr="1">
<test1>
<ptxt>Remove the thermostat (See page <xref label="Seep01" href="RM000001IPK001X"/>).</ptxt>
</test1>
<test1>
<ptxt>Check the valve opening temperature of the thermostat.</ptxt>
<spec>
<title>Standard</title>
<specitem>
<ptxt>80 to 84°C (176 to 183°F)</ptxt>
</specitem>
</spec>
<atten4>
<ptxt>In addition to the above check, confirm that the valve is completely closed when the temperature is below the standard.</ptxt>
</atten4>
</test1>
<test1>
<ptxt>Reinstall the thermostat (See page <xref label="Seep02" href="RM000001IPH001X"/>).</ptxt>
</test1>
</content6>
<res>
<down ref="RM000000PFB017X_08_0002" fin="true">OK</down>
<right ref="RM000000PFB017X_08_0005" fin="true">NG</right>
</res>
</testgrp>
<testgrp id="RM000000PFB017X_08_0003">
<testtitle>GO TO DTC CHART<xref label="Seep01" href="RM000002203002X"/>
</testtitle>
</testgrp>
<testgrp id="RM000000PFB017X_08_0005">
<testtitle>REPLACE THERMOSTAT<xref label="Seep01" href="RM000001IPK001X"/>
</testtitle>
</testgrp>
<testgrp id="RM000000PFB017X_08_0002">
<testtitle>REPLACE ENGINE COOLANT TEMPERATURE SENSOR<xref label="Seep01" href="RM0000027V1000X"/>
</testtitle>
</testgrp>
</subpara>
